id: jf-mqpo
title: "Ship a secure, maintainable, fully tracked jellyfin-cli"
description: "Establish repository-local pm governance and bring jellyfin-cli to a clean, secure, current, and verified state across runtime behavior, dependencies, CI workflows, documentation, and release readiness."
type: Goal
status: open
priority: 0
tags[4]: governance,maintenance,quality,security
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:49:03.573Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T20:10:31.162Z"
author: codex
estimated_minutes: 10080
acceptance_criteria: "Repository-local .agents/pm is initialized and committed with durable .toon items and .jsonl history.; All actionable security, dependency, code, CI, and documentation findings are fixed or explicitly documented with rationale.; The final pushed head passes the complete release verification surface."
value: Protect users and maintainers while keeping the agent-oriented Jellyfin CLI dependable and releasable.
impact: "Eliminates known dependency exposure, fixes user-visible output defects, and creates durable project lineage."
outcome: "Zero actionable dependency alerts, green release validation, resolved product defects, and complete repository-local pm history."
why_now: GitHub reports critical/high dependency alerts and issue #23 documents broken session output behavior.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T19:52:52.955Z",codex-jellyfin,"The full project graph is connected (38 nodes, 56 edges, no active isolates or sparse active nodes). This delivery lane has verified the local Jellyfin 10.11.11 contract safely; production readiness is not claimed while coverage and remaining quality-gate features are still active."
  "2026-07-21T20:04:32.102Z",codex-jellyfin,"Project ownership validation is now complete: all 206 curated repository artifacts are linked through this goal, required metadata is complete, pm validation has no warnings, and the 38-node relationship graph has no audit findings. Four implementation/interface items closed with exact acceptance evidence; coverage and the full static-analysis matrix remain active."
